  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose: To investigate the diagnostic accuracy of 18F-FLT PET for the suspicious lesions
      on mammograms and ultrasound.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      1. To investigate the diagnostic accuracy of 18F-FLT PET for the suspicious lesions on
           mammograms and ultrasound, using the pathologic result of biopsy as gold standard, and
           to determine whether 18F-FLT PET can increase the specificity in breast lesion diagnosis
           and thus reduce the unnecessary biopsy.

        2. To evaluate whether 18F-FLT PET is a cost-effective imaging modality for breast cancer
           diagnosis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
